u sulit nu Amilika Puff Kuo (Chinese: ; pinyin: Guō Xuěfú) is a Taiwanese actress, singer, model, and the youngest member of Taiwanese girl group Dream Girls. In 2008, Kuo was scouted by talent agents and in 2010, she joined girl group Dream Girls. In 2011, Dream Girls released their debut EP and in the same year, Kuo appeared in her debut television series Inborn Pair.
